{
  "text": "The mean OH* images for cases 1B and 1H are shown in Figs. 12(a) and 13(a). As discussed in Ref. [CITATION_1] , the cavity stabilized reaction zone begins at the upstream edge of the cavity shear layer and spreads into the premixed reactants at an approximately constant angle (initially). The spreading angle is set by the flame speed and the flow speed. At downstream locations, the spreading angle decreases as the flow velocity increases (shown in Figs. 9 and 10) .",
